                  </span></div><br><div class="comment">
                  <span class="c00">You can enter into a contract for almost anything you&#x27;d like, if you don&#x27;t like the terms you don&#x27;t have to agree (and thus not get the money).<p>&gt; This would be akin to telling my dad that I will gift him a car for his birthday, but on the condition that he can never sell it or rent it out or re-gift it to his friend. If he doesn&#x27;t do as I say, I&#x27;ll sue him to get the gift (car) back.<p>I think it&#x27;s more like an agreement that you can use the car as long as you keep your grades up and obey a curfew.<span>
